Data: Channel Redundancy check while initializing PluginName Plugin
This test is to check if the channel names in PluginName Plugin are unique while initializing it in different scenario.

Action:
Click the Add button in test configuration.
Select PluginName(01) and click Add.
Expected Result:
# The plugin"PluginName(01)" will be added in the configuration tree.
 # PluginName(01) panel will be loaded.
 # In Channels page default unique channel names will be present as shown in the attachment

Action:
# Again Click the Add button in test configuration.
 # Select PluginName(01) and click Add.
Expected Result:
# The plugin"PluginName(02)" will be added in the configuration tree.
 # PluginName(02) panel will be loaded.
 # In Channels page default unique channel names will be present as shown in the attachment

Action:
# Click PluginName(01) Plugin and From Menu bar select Favouties and select Export 
 # Save this as "PluginName(01) Export"
Expected Result: 1.A new xml with plugin PluginName(01) is created.

Action:
# From Menu bar, select Import and select the file "PluginName(01) Export" 
 # In the pop up select PluginName(01) Plugin and select Add
 # Select Add new in the next pop up.
Expected Result: 1. A new PluginName(03) Plugin with unique channel names are created. Refer the attachment.

Action:
# Save the configuration as *PluginName(01) Plugin init* .
 # Crate a new configuration as "*PluginName(01) Import Replace.xml*" add PluginName(01) plugin and edit all the channel names as shown in the attachment.
Expected Result: # A new xml with a plugin PluginName(01) with the edited channel names is created.

Action:
# Click Channel Redundancy check while initializing PluginName(01) Plugin and From Menu bar select Favouties and select Export 
 # Save this as "PluginName(01) Export Replace"
# Save Configuration
Expected Result: 1.A new xml with plugin PluginName(01) is created.

Action:
# Open the xml *PluginName(01) Plugin init* from File–> Open Configuration.
 # Note the channels in PluginName(01) plugin.
 # Press Ctrl+I and select *PluginName(01) Export Replace* xml and select PluginName(01) click add and Replace in the successive pop ups.
Expected Result: # The plugin PluginName(01) will be replaced and the unique channel names should create. Refer the attachment.

Action:
# Save the configuration.
 # Click the Add button in Test configuration.
 # Press control and select PluginName(01) , Kern, Average, Sartorius and Sequencer.
 # Click Add button.
 # Click PluginName(04) and save the configuration.
Expected Result:
# The plugins PluginName(04) Kern (01), Sartorius (01), Average (01) and Sequencer (01) will be added in the configuration tree.
 # PluginName(04) panel will be loaded.
 # In Channels page default channel names and parameters will be present as shown in the attachment

Action:
# Press Ctrl+O and select *PluginName(01)Import Replace.xml*
 # Select PluginName(01) plugin
Expected Result:
# The *PluginName(01)Import Replace.xml* will be loaded in Labsys
 # The plugin *PluginName(01)* will be loaded in the subpanel.
 # In the channels tab, the channel names in the xml should retain.

Action:
# Stop the application 
 # Launch again and Select *PluginName(01)* plugin.
Expected Result: # Labsys should relaunch , in *PluginName(01)* the channel name should retain as in the xml.
